00:28:30.470 --> 00:28:31.970
that requires a tensor.

00:28:31.970 --> 00:28:33.670
But no.

00:28:33.670 --> 00:28:36.530
We probably don't really
think of what we mean

00:28:36.530 --> 00:28:37.530
when we say a field.

00:28:37.530 --> 00:28:40.380
When we say an electric field,
you think of an e-vector.

00:28:40.380 --> 00:28:41.560
You think of a vector.

00:28:41.560 --> 00:28:47.520
But what a field is is just a
set of coordinates, XYZ, and

00:28:47.520 --> 00:28:49.820
that describes an area
or a volume.

00:28:49.820 --> 00:28:54.340
And just like the things that
corn grow in are referred to

00:28:54.340 --> 00:28:57.860
as corn fields, it's an area
that has corn on a lattice

00:28:57.860 --> 00:28:59.980
very often also.

00:28:59.980 --> 00:29:04.460
So a field is just a set of
coordinates in space to which

00:29:04.460 --> 00:29:07.310
a value of something
is a sign.

00:29:07.310 --> 00:29:10.430
So if we have an electric field,
and we express that

00:29:10.430 --> 00:29:13.480
electric field as a function
of X, Y, and Z, that is a

00:29:13.480 --> 00:29:15.090
field of vectors.

00:29:15.090 --> 00:29:19.540
If we take something that
has intrinsically, that

00:29:19.540 --> 00:29:22.650
intrinsically needs to be
described as a tensor, then we

00:29:22.650 --> 00:29:28.000
have to every point in space XYZ
a tensor sigma IJ, whose

00:29:28.000 --> 00:29:31.610
value and whose components
value vary with position

00:29:31.610 --> 00:29:32.700
within the space.

00:29:32.700 --> 00:29:38.810
So talking about the field as
assigning values of something

00:29:38.810 --> 00:29:44.760
to every coordinate in the space
that could be a tensor.

00:29:44.760 --> 00:29:47.370
What we refer to as an electric
field really is a

00:29:47.370 --> 00:29:48.430
field vector.

00:29:48.430 --> 00:29:51.790
So that's Nye's term, but the
fact that it took me three

00:29:51.790 --> 00:29:55.220
minutes to explain why he uses
it explains as well why I

00:29:55.220 --> 00:29:56.090
don't care for it.

00:29:56.090 --> 00:29:58.880
So we'll talk about these
as property tensors.

00:29:58.880 --> 00:30:04.040
And property tensors are
something that's

00:30:04.040 --> 00:30:05.000
innate to the material.

00:30:05.000 --> 00:30:09.550
Something like stress, strain,
and other second rank tensors

00:30:09.550 --> 00:30:18.110
are external stimuli, just
like an electric field.

00:30:18.110 --> 00:30:23.510
And they have value that is
imposed on the crystal, and

00:30:23.510 --> 00:30:28.000
the stress field is defined
as a function of position.

00:30:28.000 --> 00:30:31.000
So that's the distinction
between a property tensor,

00:30:31.000 --> 00:30:34.690
which is subject to symmetry
constraints, and a tensor that

00:30:34.690 --> 00:30:38.390
represents a stimulus, an
external stimulus applied to

00:30:38.390 --> 00:30:42.320
the crystal, and it's defined
as a function of position.

00:30:42.320 --> 00:30:45.360
And that is a field tensor.

00:30:45.360 --> 00:30:46.940
OK, so that's the difference.

00:30:46.940 --> 00:30:49.640
Since this is something that's
imposed externally, it can

00:30:49.640 --> 00:30:52.760
have any form of the tensor
that you wish to oppose.

00:30:52.760 --> 00:30:56.300
And there are no symmetry
restrictions on it.

00:30:56.300 --> 00:30:58.760
The only restriction is, as
we'll show next time, that it

00:30:58.760 --> 00:31:02.401
must be symmetric if the body
is to be in equilibrium.

